    Ingredients:

    Pure Arabica Coffee, Caffeine & Cold Pressed Coconut Oil

    Directions:

    Scoop a spoonful of the Coffee Body Scrub and apply it on wet body. Gently scrub the body in circular motions to exfoliate and remove tan. Focus on troublesome areas such as the neck, elbows, underarms and feet. Rinse with warm water, pat dry and follow up with Coffee Body Lotion or Choco Body Butter.

    Product Description


    Exfoliates & Removes Tan, Dirt, Ingrown Hair and Dead Skin

    Our body accumulates dead skin cells over a period of time which leads to skin issues like dullness, roughness and patchy skin. Hence, it becomes necessary to exfoliate regularly for fresh, soft & smooth skin. India's original Coffee Body Scrub with perfectly sized Coffee particles, exfoliates and gently gets rid of dead skin from the entire body including troublesome areas such as the neck, knees, elbows, underarms and feet.

    • Exfoliates & Removes Dead Skin
    • Removes Tan
    • Makes the Skin Soft & Smooth
    • Removes Cellulite & Ingrown Hair
    • Hassle-free & Easy to Use

    India's Original Coffee Body Scrub for Soft & Smooth Skin

    What Makes It So Good?

    With Coffee at its heart, it is also effective in tan removal & cellulite reduction. Coffee Body Scrub has Coffee that exfoliates & removes tan while Coconut Oil nourishes and moisturizes. Suitable for all skin types, this Coffee-infused wonder is easy to use, hassle-free and much more effective as compared to homemade scrubs.

    How To Use For Best Results

    Apply the Coffee Body Scrub & rub in circular motions

    Focus on the neck, elbows, knees, underarms & feet

    Rinse, pat dry & follow up with Coffee Body Lotion

    Frequently Asked Questions

    Why should I exfoliate at all?

    Our body sheds dead skin cells regularly and if not removed, it leads to dullness, roughness, clogged pores and patchy skin. So, it is recommended to exfoliate to keep the skin soft & smooth.

    Is Coffee good for exfoliation?

    Coffee is considered as one of the best exfoliators and Coffee Body Scrub is loaded with it. With its perfectly sized particles, it gets rid of dead skin and tan effortlessly.

    What is the difference between Face & Body Scrub?

    The difference between the two is that face scrub is gentler than body scrub. Hence, we recommend you to choose a face scrub to exfoliate your face as its skin is more sensitive than the body.

    What skin type is it suitable for?

    The Naked and Raw Coffee Body Scrub is suitable for normal to oily skin types. For dry skin, we recommend using a moisturizer after using the body scrub.
